---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us"
  description="Learn about Meadow Vista Trails Association — dedicated to establishing and maintaining safe trails in Meadow Vista and the surrounding foothill areas since 1995."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">About MVTA</h1>

    <div class="prose-content mt-8">
      <p>
        Meadow Vista Trails Association (MVTA) is dedicated to establishing and maintaining
        safe trails in Meadow Vista and the surrounding areas. Founded in 1995, we serve
        individuals interested in walking, dog walking, jogging, running, bike riding, and
        horseback riding throughout the foothill communities of Placer County.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        Creating trails and community in Meadow Vista since 1995. We believe that access
        to safe, well-maintained trails enriches the lives of residents and visitors alike,
        connecting people with the natural beauty of the Sierra Nevada foothills.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Trail maintenance</strong> — volunteer work parties keep existing trails
          safe and accessible for hikers, cyclists, and equestrians.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Trail development</strong> — we advocate for and help develop new trail
          connections in the Meadow Vista area.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Facilities management</strong> — we manage the Meadow Vista Horse Arena
          and adjacent Dog Park on Combie Road, on land owned by Placer County.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Community events</strong> — group hikes, board meetings, and participation
          in local events like Pioneer Day.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Education</strong> — our newsletter and blog keep members informed about
          local trails, environmental stewardship, and conservation.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Membership</h2>
      <p>
        MVTA is a member-supported nonprofit. Your membership directly funds trail
        maintenance, facility upkeep, and community programs. Membership levels:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Individual</strong> — $25/year</li>
        <li><strong>Family</strong> — $35/year</li>
        <li><strong>Trail Guardian</strong> — $100/year</li>
        <li><strong>Lifetime Sponsor</strong> — $1,000</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <a href="/contact">Join MVTA today</a> to support trails in your community.
      </p>

      <h2>Governance</h2>
      <p>
        MVTA is governed by a volunteer board of nine members elected by the membership.
        Elections are held in November or December of odd-numbered years, and board members
        serve two-year terms. Learn more about our current <a href="/board">board of directors</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Mailing address: P.O. Box 871, Meadow Vista, CA 95722<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:admin@mvtrails.org">admin@mvtrails.org</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
